**Key observations:**
- `/hbw/unload @ hbw_2` has extremely high queue time (mean 386.82s, median 358.98s) — this is the system entry point, so "queue time" reflects inter-arrival gaps between workpieces.
- `/hbw/store_empty_bucket @ hbw_1` (n=1) shows 132.55s queue — likely an anomalous single observation.
- **vgr_1** has the highest queue time among processing resources (mean 33.41s), reflecting its role as the primary interconnect serving both lanes.
- Most processing resources have queue times of 3–7s, indicating low contention during this 2-hour observation window.

